radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is enlarged, measuring 13 mm in greatest diameter, surrounded by mesenteric fat stranding. No contrast seen within the appendix. The bases of the lungs are clear, no focal lesions in the liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, or kidneys. Normal stomach, duodenum, and small bowel without evidence of obstruction. No evidence of appendiceal rupture. Normal pelvic structures.
